
postfix-init: 

	setup /etc/postfix/virtual-available/ and /etc/postfix/virtual-enabled/ (similar to Apache in Debian/Ubuntu)

postfix-disable-site: 

	similar to a2ensite in Debian/Ubuntu Apache


postfix-enable-site: 

	similar to a2dissite in Debian/Ubuntu Apache


postfix-create-virtual: 

	create /etc/postfix/virtual and /etc/postfix/virtual_alias_domains



Each site file in /etc/postfix/virtual-available/ should have the same name as
the domain name (e.g. virtual-alias.domain) and follow the format in
http://www.postfix.org/virtual.5.html except that @virtual-alias.domain must be
omitted.

